data.description:
Comforts of mountain living in this thoughtfully updated 2-bedroom, 3-bathroom home. The kitchen has been recently renovated and features a convenient pantry, and the loft bedroom has also seen recent upgrades. Tongue and Groove ceilings add a touch of charm, while the dining/sunroom—complete with tiled floors and a wood stove—serves as a cozy retreat. French doors seamlessly blend indoor and outdoor living, revealing a landscape abundant with diverse birdlife and wildflowers, all without knapweed.

The lower level introduces more versatility with extra living space featuring a wet bar, an additional bedroom with a spacious walk-in closet, and a bathroom with heated tile floors. Commercial spray foam in the basement deadens sound throughout the home, and passive solar south-facing windows make the home energy-efficient. Because of the basement, the home remains pleasantly cool in the summer months. Outdoors, a 30’x40’ pole building holds promise for various uses, including easy conversion into a barn. The land offers enough space for a guest house or additional building, requiring only an electrical permit for construction. Additional features include a ready-to-use chicken coop and a fire pit, perfect for outdoor gatherings. With direct access to the back road to Tally Lake and miles of state lands right at your doorstep, this location is ideal for outdoor enthusiasts and those with recreational vehicles. It's the perfect spot if you love your toys—you can even drive your ATV straight from here.

Located just 10 minutes from Kalispell, you have easy access to numerous amenities. The landscape has been thoughtfully thinned to provide both privacy and a natural setting. Experience a balanced lifestyle where comfort meets the beauty of nature. Call Kara Chapman (406) 407-7509 or your Real Estate Professional.
